            {
              "id": "JS-AUDIT-025",
              "name": "Conditional current-password check + CSRF + password-in-query in changePassword",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "Conditional current-password check + CSRF + password-in-query in changePassword"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "If `current` is absent the check is *skipped entirely*, allowing any session holder to set a new password without proving knowledge of the old one. The route is GET (line uses req.query — confirmed by CodeQL alerts 14-16 'js/sensitive-get-query'), so any cross-origin `<img src=/rest/user/change-password?new=hacked&repeat=hacked>` performs the change with the victim's ambient cookie token. No CSRF protection. Passwords also end up in browser history, proxies, and access logs."
              },
              "help": {
                "text": "Recommended fix: Change method to POST/PATCH, require current password, add CSRF protection (SameSite=strict cookies + CSRF token / double-submit). Read password from body, never the query string.",
                "markdown": "## Conditional current-password check + CSRF + password-in-query in changePassword\n\n**CWE:** CWE-620\n\n**OWASP:** A07:2021-Identification and Authentication Failures\n\n### Exploitation\n\nIf `current` is absent the check is *skipped entirely*, allowing any session holder to set a new password without proving knowledge of the old one. The route is GET (line uses req.query — confirmed by CodeQL alerts 14-16 'js/sensitive-get-query'), so any cross-origin `<img src=/rest/user/change-password?new=hacked&repeat=hacked>` performs the change with the victim's ambient cookie token. No CSRF protection. Passwords also end up in browser history, proxies, and access logs.\n\n### Recommended Fix\n\nChange method to POST/PATCH, require current password, add CSRF protection (SameSite=strict cookies + CSRF token / double-submit). Read password from body, never the query string."
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "error"
              },
              "properties": {
                "security-severity": "9.6",
                "tags": [
                  "csrf",
                  "auth_flaw",
                  "tier2"
                ],
                "precision": "high",
                "cwe": [
                  "CWE-620"
                ],
                "owasp": [
                  "A07:2021-Identification and Authentication Failures"
                ],
                "triage": "confirmed"
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "JS-AUDIT-026",
              "name": "Reset-password rate limiter keys on attacker-controllable X-Forwarded-For",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "Reset-password rate limiter keys on attacker-controllable X-Forwarded-For"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "`app.enable('trust proxy')` (line 342) plus a header-derived rate-limit key allows an attacker to rotate X-Forwarded-For on every request, making the limit ineffective. This unblocks security-answer guessing against /rest/user/reset-password (combined with JS-AUDIT-005 hardcoded HMAC secret, full account takeover is feasible)."
              },
              "help": {
                "text": "Recommended fix: Use a trustworthy proxy chain (Express trust proxy with concrete proxy IPs) and key off req.ip post-trust. Add account-level lockout / CAPTCHA.",
                "markdown": "## Reset-password rate limiter keys on attacker-controllable X-Forwarded-For\n\n**CWE:** CWE-307\n\n**OWASP:** A07:2021-Identification and Authentication Failures\n\n### Exploitation\n\n`app.enable('trust proxy')` (line 342) plus a header-derived rate-limit key allows an attacker to rotate X-Forwarded-For on every request, making the limit ineffective. This unblocks security-answer guessing against /rest/user/reset-password (combined with JS-AUDIT-005 hardcoded HMAC secret, full account takeover is feasible).\n\n### Recommended Fix\n\nUse a trustworthy proxy chain (Express trust proxy with concrete proxy IPs) and key off req.ip post-trust. Add account-level lockout / CAPTCHA."
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "warning"
              },
              "properties": {
                "security-severity": "5.3",
                "tags": [
                  "missing_rate_limit",
                  "tier2"
                ],
                "precision": "high",
                "cwe": [
                  "CWE-307"
                ],
                "owasp": [
                  "A07:2021-Identification and Authentication Failures"
                ],
                "triage": "confirmed"
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "JS-AUDIT-027",
              "name": "Unauthenticated full configuration dump on /rest/admin/application-configuration",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "Unauthenticated full configuration dump on /rest/admin/application-configuration"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "The route is mounted at server.ts:605 with no auth and serializes the entire `config` object — leaking application secrets that may be present in node-config layers (challenge keys, hashes, ctf flags, etc.). 'admin' in the path is purely cosmetic."
              },
              "help": {
                "text": "Recommended fix: Place behind admin auth; return only non-sensitive subkeys.",
                "markdown": "## Unauthenticated full configuration dump on /rest/admin/application-configuration\n\n**CWE:** CWE-200\n\n**OWASP:** A05:2021-Security Misconfiguration\n\n### Exploitation\n\nThe route is mounted at server.ts:605 with no auth and serializes the entire `config` object — leaking application secrets that may be present in node-config layers (challenge keys, hashes, ctf flags, etc.). 'admin' in the path is purely cosmetic.\n\n### Recommended Fix\n\nPlace behind admin auth; return only non-sensitive subkeys."
