            {
              "id": "JS-AUDIT-031",
              "name": "Wide-open CORS — `app.use(cors())` with no origin allow-list",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "Wide-open CORS — `app.use(cors())` with no origin allow-list"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Default cors() reflects the request Origin and responds with Access-Control-Allow-Origin matching any caller. Combined with cookie-based JWT (security.updateAuthenticatedUsers reads req.cookies.token) and bearer tokens in localStorage, any third-party page can read responses cross-origin. This nullifies same-origin protections for the entire API."
              },
              "help": {
                "text": "Recommended fix: Configure cors() with an explicit origins allow-list (production frontend host only), credentials:false unless required, and a strict allowed-methods/headers list.",
                "markdown": "## Wide-open CORS — `app.use(cors())` with no origin allow-list\n\n**CWE:** CWE-942\n\n**OWASP:** A05:2021-Security Misconfiguration\n\n### Exploitation\n\nDefault cors() reflects the request Origin and responds with Access-Control-Allow-Origin matching any caller. Combined with cookie-based JWT (security.updateAuthenticatedUsers reads req.cookies.token) and bearer tokens in localStorage, any third-party page can read responses cross-origin. This nullifies same-origin protections for the entire API.\n\n### Recommended Fix\n\nConfigure cors() with an explicit origins allow-list (production frontend host only), credentials:false unless required, and a strict allowed-methods/headers list."
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "error"
              },
              "properties": {
                "security-severity": "7.4",
                "tags": [
                  "cors_misconfiguration",
                  "tier3"
                ],
                "precision": "high",
                "cwe": [
                  "CWE-942"
                ],
                "owasp": [
                  "A05:2021-Security Misconfiguration"
                ],
                "triage": "confirmed"
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "JS-AUDIT-032",
              "name": "Slash-collapse middleware breaks downstream path-based protections",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "Slash-collapse middleware breaks downstream path-based protections"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Globally rewriting req.url after Express parses it can desynchronise router matching from the URL the application thinks it is serving (e.g. for swagger, static files, and HTTP cache keys). Combined with the redirect/file-server allowlists that match on substrings, this provides additional bypass surface."
              },
              "help": {
                "text": "Recommended fix: Use express-slash or perform path normalisation at the edge / reverse proxy, not after routing decisions.",
                "markdown": "## Slash-collapse middleware breaks downstream path-based protections\n\n**CWE:** CWE-444\n\n**OWASP:** A05:2021-Security Misconfiguration\n\n### Exploitation\n\nGlobally rewriting req.url after Express parses it can desynchronise router matching from the URL the application thinks it is serving (e.g. for swagger, static files, and HTTP cache keys). Combined with the redirect/file-server allowlists that match on substrings, this provides additional bypass surface.\n\n### Recommended Fix\n\nUse express-slash or perform path normalisation at the edge / reverse proxy, not after routing decisions."
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "warning"
              },
              "properties": {
                "security-severity": "5.3",
                "tags": [
                  "request_smuggling_adjacent",
                  "tier3"
                ],
                "precision": "medium",
                "cwe": [
                  "CWE-444"
                ],
                "owasp": [
                  "A05:2021-Security Misconfiguration"
                ],
                "triage": "confirmed"
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "JS-AUDIT-033",
              "name": "Dev `errorhandler` middleware mounted in production — stack trace exposure",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "Dev `errorhandler` middleware mounted in production — stack trace exposure"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "The `errorhandler` package is intended for development; it renders full HTML stack traces including local file paths, source lines, and stack frames. It is mounted unconditionally. Many routes intentionally call next(err) on edge cases, leaking implementation detail and aiding further attack. CodeQL js/stack-trace-exposure flags individual instances too (alerts 7-13)."
              },
              "help": {
                "text": "Recommended fix: Mount only when process.env.NODE_ENV === 'development'; use a JSON error responder in production that hides stack frames.",
                "markdown": "## Dev `errorhandler` middleware mounted in production — stack trace exposure\n\n**CWE:** CWE-209\n\n**OWASP:** A05:2021-Security Misconfiguration\n\n### Exploitation\n\nThe `errorhandler` package is intended for development; it renders full HTML stack traces including local file paths, source lines, and stack frames. It is mounted unconditionally. Many routes intentionally call next(err) on edge cases, leaking implementation detail and aiding further attack. CodeQL js/stack-trace-exposure flags individual instances too (alerts 7-13).\n\n### Recommended Fix\n\nMount only when process.env.NODE_ENV === 'development'; use a JSON error responder in production that hides stack frames."
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "warning"
              },
              "properties": {
                "security-severity": "5.3",
                "tags": [
                  "verbose_error",
                  "tier3"
                ],
                "precision": "high",
                "cwe": [
                  "CWE-209"
                ],
                "owasp": [
                  "A05:2021-Security Misconfiguration"
                ],
                "triage": "confirmed"
              }
            },
