            {
              "id": "JS-AUDIT-035",
              "name": "Path traversal in /encryptionkeys/:file, /support/logs/:file, /ftp/:file",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "Path traversal in /encryptionkeys/:file, /support/logs/:file, /ftp/:file"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Disallowing only '/' is insufficient — '%2e%2e%2f' and other encodings, and on some platforms '\\\\', bypass the filter. servePublicFiles additionally allows the literal `incident-support.kdbx`, exposing a KeePass database, and uses `cutOffPoisonNullByte` to enable %00-truncation attacks on its extension allowlist (so attacker can serve any file by appending `.md%00`). serveLogFiles and serveKeyFiles use the same naive `/`-only guard."
              },
              "help": {
                "text": "Recommended fix: Use a strict allowlist of filenames or `decodeURIComponent` + `path.normalize` + startsWith(root) check + explicit extension whitelist.",
                "markdown": "## Path traversal in /encryptionkeys/:file, /support/logs/:file, /ftp/:file\n\n**CWE:** CWE-22\n\n**OWASP:** A01:2021-Broken Access Control\n\n### Exploitation\n\nDisallowing only '/' is insufficient — '%2e%2e%2f' and other encodings, and on some platforms '\\\\', bypass the filter. servePublicFiles additionally allows the literal `incident-support.kdbx`, exposing a KeePass database, and uses `cutOffPoisonNullByte` to enable %00-truncation attacks on its extension allowlist (so attacker can serve any file by appending `.md%00`). serveLogFiles and serveKeyFiles use the same naive `/`-only guard.\n\n### Recommended Fix\n\nUse a strict allowlist of filenames or `decodeURIComponent` + `path.normalize` + startsWith(root) check + explicit extension whitelist."
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "error"
              },
              "properties": {
                "security-severity": "7.5",
                "tags": [
                  "path_traversal",
                  "tier2"
                ],
                "precision": "high",
                "cwe": [
                  "CWE-22"
                ],
                "owasp": [
                  "A01:2021-Broken Access Control"
                ],
                "triage": "confirmed"
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "JS-AUDIT-036",
              "name": "Template object injection / LFR via dataErasure layout parameter",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "Template object injection / LFR via dataErasure layout parameter"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "req.body is spread into hbs locals and req.body.layout influences template lookup. A targeted `layout` value can pull arbitrary file content into the rendered view (the code itself solves lfrChallenge). The denylist is substring-based and case-toggled, so encodings or unrelated paths still slip through."
              },
              "help": {
                "text": "Recommended fix: Do not allow client to pick the layout. Use a fixed layout name.",
                "markdown": "## Template object injection / LFR via dataErasure layout parameter\n\n**CWE:** CWE-73\n\n**OWASP:** A03:2021-Injection\n\n### Exploitation\n\nreq.body is spread into hbs locals and req.body.layout influences template lookup. A targeted `layout` value can pull arbitrary file content into the rendered view (the code itself solves lfrChallenge). The denylist is substring-based and case-toggled, so encodings or unrelated paths still slip through.\n\n### Recommended Fix\n\nDo not allow client to pick the layout. Use a fixed layout name."
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "warning"
              },
              "properties": {
                "security-severity": "6.1",
                "tags": [
                  "lfr",
                  "template_injection",
