              "id": "JS-AUDIT-047",
              "name": "currentUser allows client-selected fields (password leak via ?fields=password)",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "currentUser allows client-selected fields (password leak via ?fields=password)"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "The /rest/user/whoami endpoint lets the caller pick which user-object fields are returned via `?fields=...`. There is no allow-list, so `?fields=password,totpSecret` returns the user's MD5 hash and TOTP secret. The route even includes a `passwordHashLeakChallenge` that solves on success, proving exploitability."
              },
              "help": {
                "text": "Recommended fix: Replace dynamic field projection with a static, allow-listed subset (id, email, profileImage, lastLoginIp).",
                "markdown": "## currentUser allows client-selected fields (password leak via ?fields=password)\n\n**CWE:** CWE-200\n\n**OWASP:** A01:2021-Broken Access Control\n\n### Exploitation\n\nThe /rest/user/whoami endpoint lets the caller pick which user-object fields are returned via `?fields=...`. There is no allow-list, so `?fields=password,totpSecret` returns the user's MD5 hash and TOTP secret. The route even includes a `passwordHashLeakChallenge` that solves on success, proving exploitability.\n\n### Recommended Fix\n\nReplace dynamic field projection with a static, allow-listed subset (id, email, profileImage, lastLoginIp)."
              },
