        {
          "ruleId": "JS-AUDIT-007",
          "level": "error",
          "message": {
            "text": "`denyAll` is wired into critical routes (PUT/DELETE /api/Users/:id, DELETE /api/Products/:id, /api/Challenges, /api/Hints, /api/SecurityQuestions, /api/Recycles/:id, etc.). Because of the express-jwt 0.1.3 alg:none bug above, a token with `alg:none` would skip secret validation entirely. Even without that, Math.random() is non-cryptographic and predictable; an attacker who can guess one secret can mint tokens. The bigger issue is that 'deny all' is implemented as 'verify with a random secret' instead of a hard 403, which is fundamentally wrong."
          },
          "locations": [
            {
              "physicalLocation": {
                "artifactLocation": {
                  "uri": "lib/insecurity.ts",
                  "uriBaseId": "%SRCROOT%"
                },
