          "ruleId": "JS-AUDIT-008",
          "level": "error",
          "message": {
            "text": "isRedirectAllowed() returns true if the *attacker-supplied URL* contains an allowlisted string anywhere. Therefore `/redirect?to=https://evil.example.com/?x=https://github.com/juice-shop/juice-shop` passes the check and the server returns a 302 to evil.example.com. Used for phishing / credential harvesting / token exfil. CodeQL (alert 3) confirms."
          },
